Durban - An office below the Marine Sands building caught alight in North Beach, Durban on Wednesday. 
 
 
  Durban Fire and Emergency services converged on the scene to find smoke coming from the parking lot area. 
 
 
  
 
 
  Construction works said they were putting water proofing on the roof and had gone on a lunch break. They then noticed smoke coming from the roof top. 
 
 
  
 
 
  Trevor Stevens, the Durban Central Fire department  Divisional Commander  said timber caught alight under the roof where workers had been working. 
 
 
  
 
 
